Description: PCL is a standalone, large scale, open project for 2D/3D image and point cloud processing.
Headquarters Regions: San Francisco Bay Area, Silicon Valley, West Coast
Full Description: The Point Cloud Library (or PCL) is a large scale, open project [1] for 2D/3D image and point cloud processing. The PCL framework contains numerous state-of-the art algorithms including filtering, feature estimation, surface reconstruction, registration, model fitting and segmentation. These algorithms can be used, for example, to filter outliers from noisy data, stitch 3D point clouds together, segment relevant parts of a scene, extract keypoints and compute descriptors to recognize objects in the world based on their geometric appearance, and create surfaces from point clouds and visualize them -- to name a few.   PCL is released under the terms of the 3-clause BSD license and is open source software. It is free for commercial and research use. PCL is cross-platform, and has been successfully compiled and deployed on Linux, MacOS, Windows, and Android/iOS. To simplify development, PCL is split into a series of smaller code libraries, that can be compiled separately. This modularity is important for distributing PCL on platforms with reduced computational or size constraints (for more information about each module see the documentation page). Another way to think about PCL is as a graph of code libraries, similar to the Boost set of C++ libraries
Industry Groups: Data and Analytics, Information Technology, Sales and Marketing, Software

Description: ThanksBud, Inc. will revolutionize the service industry by updating the process by which people purchase services. ThanksBud, Inc. will
Headquarters Regions: Southern US
Full Description: ThanksBud, Inc. will revolutionize the service industry by updating the process by which people purchase services.  ThanksBud, Inc. will organize the numerous service providers that make up the service industry into a easy to use, online, instantly accessible network that allows our customers to buy cheap, affordable service with the confidence of hiring someone with proven work ethic and ability.   ThanksBud Inc., is an online marketplace that will bring together the world of technology to the service industry.  ThanksBud Inc., will do for the service industry what Ebay did to the garage sale.  ThanksBud Inc., will provide a community where users can search providers, offer them jobs simultaneously, and receive services for a fraction of the cost. The yellow pages used to be the only way to find a deal and a person would have to go through them all and call each provider.  Now, with ThanksBud Inc., a potential customer can go to one place online, read provider credentials and reviews, describe the job one time, and ask for a price that is lower than they most likely would pay by just calling the first person in the phone book.  Most importantly, this process will be free for the user.  Further, the small service provider will be able to access the advantage that the larger companies have of always having a steady workflow to choose from.  If times are slow, the provider can accept a job from ThanksBud.com and make money instead of just sitting around and waiting for someone to pick up a phone book.  ThanksBud Inc., will also allow the provider to offer good deals to the users in order to boosts offers.   In addition, ThanksBud Inc. is bringing cell phone usage into play with the quick and easy text, read, and accept method for accepting jobs.  The use will describe the job and all the providers will receive a text straight to their cell phones.  A lot of service providers are not around the internet at all times and ThanksBud Inc. will bring the internet to them via cell phone text messaging.  The provider will have the convenience of securing jobs as soon as the user asks for them.   Providers will range from lawn care, to home repair, to plumbing, to computing, to building, to mechanical and electrical, to personal services, and to almost any industry imaginable.  The beauty of ThanksBud, Inc. is the expandability of the company to more and more areas of service.  The beauty of expandibility is that sales can continue to increase in the already enormous market of buyers, gross margin will increase even more due to the small overhead of the company, and profits over the first five years will be through the roof.   ThanksBud Inc. has the potential to take over the lion's share of the online service industry.  The online goods industry has grown to be a trillion dollar industry in the United States alone and the service industry is just as big.  There just has not been an avenue to capture that market; until now.  ThanksBud Inc. is the online marketplace for the future of the service industry.
Founders: Anthony Johnson, RJ Martino, Roxane Martino

Description: AdvisorMed is a free, online report card for physicians, hospitals, nursing homes, and home healthcare agencies.
Headquarters Regions: Great Lakes, Midwestern US
Full Description: AdvisorMed.com is a free, online report card featuring physicians, hospitals, nursing homes and home healthcare agencies.  Our goal is to help our consumers with their healthcare choices. AdvisorMed is the place all consumers come to receive trusted unbiased information on healthcare providers. How do I select the "best" healthcare provider for my loved one? - Which surgeon should I choose to operate on my heart condition? - Will this home care provider help my dad, so he doesn't return to the hospital? - Can this hospital provide the very best care for my daughter':s illness? - Which is the best nursing home for my grandfather? Consumers are encouraged to talk to physicians, tour facilities, speak with staff, consult family members/friends, and research the internet. The problem is taking that information, processing it, to arrive at the "best" possible conclusion.   AdvisorMed has created the solution — The Favorability Index. AdvisorMed's Favorability Index ranks healthcare providers based on national standardized public data and AdvisorMed user reviews.  It helps consumers process the information to reach the "best" possible conclusion.  Our completely organic ranking system is continuously incorporating new, unbiased information based on both the good and the bad. AdvisorMed.com is long overdue.   Now consumers have complete information to make truly informed decisions.

When companies miss a quarterly number, acquire a new product, or realign their internal teams, Inqune’s methodology can be re-deployed to extract the core elements of the business, capture current standards and practices, develop innovative and interactive learning that can be implemented globally, and measure the impact in increased revenue or reduced cost. Inqune launches lean learning programs and creates training infrastructure. These programs require sophisticated design, and firms with low training frequency to have best in class content. To meet their unique needs, Inqune created a methodology specifically for cloud computing firms that allows them to rapidly develop scalable training programs.
